The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Wipro Technologies has set up an offshore development unit for Zurich Financial Services in Chennai. The two companies had signed a framework agreement earlier this year. According to the deal, Wipro will provide application development and maintenance services in seven countries. Wipro has a strong offshore delivery record. The tieup will help us consolidate our sourcing strategy, Michael Paravicinia, a senior official of Zurich Financial said. Zurich Financial is an insurance-based financial services provider and has offices in North America, Latin America, Europe and Asia Pacific.

 Magma Shrachi Finance and International Tractors have signed a memorandum of understanding to form Magma ITL Finance Ltd, a joint venture asset financing company to finance the Sonalika range of tractors. Magma will hold a 74 per cent stake in the new company.

 A private equity firm has picked up a 16 per cent stake in Liberty Whiteware Ltd at a premium of Rs 145 per share. The cost of the acquisition was Rs 20 crore. Liberty Whiteware manufactures bathroom products and accessories made of ceramics.

 Mitsubishi Heavy Industries India Precision Tools, a subsidiary of Mitsubishi Heavy Industries Ltd, Japan, has set up a manufacturing facility at Ranipet near Chennai. The plant, built at an investment of around Rs 50 crore, will double the companys capacity.

 Bank of India (BoI) has entered into an alliance with Franklin Templeton Investments (India) to distribute the latters mutual fund products in the country.

 Tata Power Company has signed an EPC contract with Toshiba Corporation to supply five 800mw steam turbine generators for the 4,000mw power project at Mundra, Gujarat.

 MSD India, a wholly owned subsidiary of US drug maker Merck amp; Co, has launched Invanz. The drug can be used to treat patients who have developed resistance to antibiotics.

 Titan has launched an exchange offer, under which customers can exchange any old watch, irrespective of its make, age or condition, and get a 25 per cent discount on purchase of any new Titan watch. The offer is valid till September 9 at all Titan outlets.

 Airtel has launched Easy Recharge 2007 with a 365-day validity for customers in Calcutta, Bengal, Sikkim and the Andaman and Nicobar Islands. The offer includes a talktime worth Rs 1,786.

